OL,6,FThe judge referred to her as a "Z-
OL,7,Flist" celebrity whose conduct had been
OL,8,Freprehensible.
OL,10,F"She departed for America and has been
OL,11,Fawkward and difficult throughout this
OL,12,Fprocess... she has simply brazened it
OL,13,Fout," he said.
OL,15,FWith no apology for retraction made,
OL,16,Fthe level of pay-out must reflect
OL,17,Fvindication for Mr Jackson.
